    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1849-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1849-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="253" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <head>
                    <seg type="margin">[701]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Preston</persName>, Secretary of the Navy, to
                                    Commander <persName type="to">Randolph</persName>, United States
                                    Navy.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy
                                    Department</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1849-09-20">
                        <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 20,
                                    1849</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The official reports of your
                                proceedings and movements with a portion of the home squadron under
                                your command, in the neighborhood of Round Island, dated 25th and
                                28th of August, and 1st and 5th of September, 1849, and the
                                inclosures relating thereto, have been received.</p>
                <p>The prompt, the decisive, and the satisfactory manner in which you
                                have executed the confidential instructions of the 9th ultimo,
                                addressed to Commodore Foxhall A. Parker, is fully approved by the
                                Department.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully, yours, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>WM. BALLARD PRESTON.</item>
                            <item>Commander <hi rend="smallcaps">Victor M.
                                                Randolph</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Commanding U.
                                                S. Ship Albany, off Pascagoula,
                                            Mississippi.</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
